13:09.688 --> 13:11.815
<i>AND Y: I have no idea</i>
<i>why Ann is upset with me.</i>

13:11.891 --> 13:14.291
But I do know she's too nice to yell
at me in front of all these people.

13:14.360 --> 13:17.056
So, I am not
leaving this bar.

13:17.129 --> 13:19.597
So, I heard you went to Indiana State.
Yes.

13:19.665 --> 13:21.064
My buddy Todd went there.
Maybe you know him.

13:21.133 --> 13:22.293
What year did
you graduate?

13:22.368 --> 13:23.460
1968.

13:23.536 --> 13:27.028
Oh! Todd graduated in 2005,
so you probably missed him.

13:28.474 --> 13:29.634
How was your
date with Leslie?

13:29.708 --> 13:32.336
We change the band name,
and then we send the demo out.

13:32.444 --> 13:34.241
We're completely ready...
Andy, let's go.

13:34.313 --> 13:35.940
Honey, I'm just
debriefing with the band.

13:36.015 --> 13:37.607
It's just gonna
be just one second.

13:37.683 --> 13:38.741
LESLIE: Hey! Hi!

13:38.818 --> 13:42.549
Whoa! Leslie Knope! I'm so glad you
made it. You have to meet my band.

13:42.621 --> 13:43.952
Okay. Hi, band!
Hey. What's going on?

13:44.023 --> 13:46.355
Oh. I'm so sorry
that I missed your songs.

13:46.425 --> 13:48.586
Is there any way that you guys could
do like an encore or something?

13:48.661 --> 13:49.650
An encore. I like it.

13:49.728 --> 13:51.127
Guys, let's get our stuff
out of the boxes. Let's go.

13:51.197 --> 13:52.323
No, no, forget it.
No, we're going home.

13:52.398 --> 13:54.025
No, don't leave.
I just got here.

13:54.099 --> 13:55.726
Yeah, she's here
with her dad.

13:55.801 --> 13:57.632
It'd be kind of rude to not
do at least one more song.

13:57.703 --> 13:58.727
Andy.

13:59.972 --> 14:02.566
(SIGHS) Okay,
let's go. Let's go.

14:03.175 --> 14:05.040
Sorry, Leslie. We're gonna go.
I'll call you tomorrow.

14:05.110 --> 14:06.270
LESLIE: Okay.
This weekend, guys.

14:08.280 --> 14:12.307
Look. Dead or asleep?

14:13.085 --> 14:15.610
Dead or asleep?

14:17.289 --> 14:20.122
George. George!

14:22.428 --> 14:23.952
(LAUGHS) Oh.

14:24.029 --> 14:26.122
Look at me,
out like a light.

14:27.566 --> 14:29.397
I think I should
head home now.

14:29.468 --> 14:30.662
Okay.

14:32.571 --> 14:33.765
It was nice to meet you.
It was fun.

14:33.839 --> 14:36.933
I had a nice time.
Don't think I'll go out with her again.

14:37.009 --> 14:39.239
There was just no spark.

14:39.311 --> 14:40.938
How did Leslie
meet her boyfriend?

14:41.013 --> 14:43.072
She used to read him books
at the senior center.

14:43.148 --> 14:44.945
Wow. How old is he?

14:45.017 --> 14:48.248
He's six, but he has Benjamin
Button Disease. BETH: Whoa.

14:48.320 --> 14:50.584
Hey, who wants to
see me climb a tree?

14:51.190 --> 14:53.158
TOM: I do!
BETH: I do!

14:55.361 --> 14:56.953
MARK: Deputy Director Knope.

14:57.763 --> 14:59.526
Where do you
think you're going?

14:59.598 --> 15:01.793
Home. It's been
a really crappy night.

15:02.401 --> 15:04.198
Have a beer with me.

15:05.804 --> 15:08.568
I can't believe my mom tried to
set me up with an 80-year-old man.

15:08.641 --> 15:09.630
(LAUGHING)

15:10.843 --> 15:13.869
I went to dinner tonight
with somebody's grandpa.

15:13.946 --> 15:16.176
You know what?
That guy was too young for you.

15:16.248 --> 15:18.409
(LAUGHS) You should be dating
guys in their early hundreds.

15:18.484 --> 15:20.247
I'm telling you,
you should be dating men

15:20.319 --> 15:22.378
that Al Roker announces
their birthdays.

15:22.454 --> 15:24.149
(LAUGHING)

15:25.958 --> 15:27.823
Hey! Congratulations
are in order.

15:27.893 --> 15:30.521
I heard that you got that
speed bump thing through.

15:30.596 --> 15:31.893
Don't make fun of me.
I'm not.

15:31.964 --> 15:35.365
Oh, yeah. I made a bump into a smaller
bump. It's a great day for America.

15:35.434 --> 15:38.267
What are you talking about?
That thing was a pain in the butt.

15:38.337 --> 15:41.795
You fixed a problem.
That's what we're supposed to do.

15:44.643 --> 15:46.702
Mark and I are really
connecting tonight.

15:46.779 --> 15:50.579
Like we connected that night
when we made love five years ago.

15:51.216 --> 15:53.514
There's actually a lot of
similarities between those two nights.

15:53.585 --> 15:57.385
That time we were also at a bar.
And he was also pretty drunk.

16:01.560 --> 16:04.654
LESLIE: If you could put anything in
the park, what would you put in there?

16:04.730 --> 16:06.095
Okay...
Don't over-think it.

16:06.532 --> 16:10.400
Keep it simple, nice shady trees,
lots of grass, benches.

16:10.936 --> 16:13.461
A picnic table?
Sure. Water feature.

16:13.539 --> 16:15.769
Like, huge rocks
to be climbing on.

16:15.841 --> 16:17.832
A play area for the kids.
God, that sounds wonderful.

16:17.910 --> 16:20.037
I would live in that park.
But then you'd be homeless.

16:20.112 --> 16:22.103
(LAUGHS) BARTENDER: Hey,
we're closing up.

16:22.181 --> 16:23.205
Oh.

16:23.282 --> 16:24.510
What time is it?
I should go.

16:24.583 --> 16:26.551
No, no, no,
no, no, no, no!

16:26.618 --> 16:29.109
We're getting drinks to go.
Come on. Beers to go!

16:29.188 --> 16:31.554
(LAUGHING) Where are we going?
All the bars are closed.

16:31.690 --> 16:33.123
(LESLIE LAUGHING)

16:35.761 --> 16:38.355
You think I can get my beer bottle
in that shopping cart right there?

16:38.430 --> 16:41.126
What? Mark, don't.
This pit isn't a dump.

16:41.200 --> 16:42.792
Yes, it is.
Look around, Leslie.

16:42.868 --> 16:44.199
I mean, there's
crap everywhere.

16:44.269 --> 16:47.170
One beer bottle is not
gonna make any difference.

16:48.807 --> 16:50.240
(LESLIE LAUGHING)

16:50.809 --> 16:53.175
Damn it!
I was so close there!

16:53.245 --> 16:55.475
Yeah, so...
It was pretty close!

16:55.547 --> 16:58.072
So far to the left!
So far to the left!

16:58.150 --> 17:00.345
You think you can do any better?
No, please.

17:00.419 --> 17:02.580
I don't want anyone to see!
I'm the Deputy Director of Parks...

17:02.654 --> 17:04.815
You're the Deputy Director
of Parks and blah blah...

17:04.890 --> 17:06.482
You know, nobody's
gonna see it.

17:06.959 --> 17:08.756
Go on and chuck it.

17:11.296 --> 17:12.819
(BOTH LAUGHING)

17:15.200 --> 17:17.599
Unbelievable!
That's unbelievable!

17:17.836 --> 17:21.101
You missed the entire pit,
which is huge, by the way.

17:21.807 --> 17:23.069
I didn't do anything wrong.

17:23.142 --> 17:24.404
You didn't do anything wrong?
Mmm-mmm.

17:24.476 --> 17:26.740
I waited on you
hand and foot.

17:26.811 --> 17:27.836
And it was exhausting!

17:27.913 --> 17:30.882
I fed you meals, and you could've
had your casts off two weeks ago!

17:30.949 --> 17:33.281
That is not true.
It's not true?

17:33.385 --> 17:35.876
So you're calling
Dr. Harris a liar?

17:36.688 --> 17:38.383
Yes.
I'm gonna call Dr. Harris right now.

17:38.457 --> 17:39.446
How about that?
You call him!

17:39.525 --> 17:41.891
You get me on the phone with Dr. Harris.
Yes. Yes. I will.

17:41.960 --> 17:43.427
Don't call him right now!

17:43.495 --> 17:45.292
ANN: Why?
Because it's late.

17:45.364 --> 17:47.195
ANDY: Listen,
just put the phone down.

17:47.266 --> 17:50.099
Fine! You want the truth?

17:50.169 --> 17:51.261
Yes.

17:52.137 --> 17:54.833
Could I have gotten my
casts off two weeks ago?

17:54.907 --> 17:58.035
Technically, yes. But

17:59.378 --> 18:01.972
I really, really like it
when you serve me food.

18:02.047 --> 18:03.810
Get out.
Get out of my house.

18:03.882 --> 18:05.213
(GROANS) But what...

18:05.284 --> 18:07.844
Take a walk with your
overly-healed legs,

18:07.920 --> 18:10.684
and let me think
about this relationship.

18:11.090 --> 18:12.523
(DOOR OPENING)

18:16.628 --> 18:20.462
LESLIE: Okay, this pit.
Give it to me straight.

18:21.433 --> 18:23.060
Are we ever gonna
turn it into a park?

18:23.135 --> 18:25.399
(LAUGHS) Leslie,
this is already a park!

18:25.471 --> 18:29.373
Look, I mean, you got
Dirt Slide over here,

18:29.441 --> 18:31.636
you got Ring Around The
Diaper you could play there.

18:31.710 --> 18:32.904
(LESLIE LAUGHING)

18:32.978 --> 18:37.074
You've got Duck, Duck, Glass
you could play right there.

18:37.649 --> 18:39.310
Mystery Trash.

18:40.319 --> 18:43.117
What's not to love about this park,
right here, now?

18:43.188 --> 18:47.249
I wish we could turn it into
a pit, frankly, don't you?

18:50.362 --> 18:52.626
But, seriously,
I mean, really?

18:53.899 --> 18:57.733
Honestly, Leslie,
it's gonna be a long, uphill battle.

18:58.437 --> 18:59.836
You are gonna
be super annoyed

18:59.905 --> 19:01.270
with all the people
that want you to fail.

19:01.340 --> 19:05.674
There is a sea of red tape,
endless roadblocks.

19:07.746 --> 19:10.374
So, yeah, I don't know.
I don't know.

19:14.820 --> 19:17.118
Screw it. I'm gonna
try to do it anyway.

19:17.189 --> 19:18.178
(BOTH LAUGHING)

19:18.924 --> 19:20.323
LESLIE: I mean,
Kennedy put a man on the moon.

19:20.392 --> 19:21.416
MARK: He did.

19:21.493 --> 19:22.790
LESLIE: I can build one park.

19:23.328 --> 19:25.489
I really admire
your tenacity.

19:26.598 --> 19:28.156
I really admire you.

19:30.202 --> 19:31.191
(SIGHS)

19:52.491 --> 19:54.550
No, no.
Wait, what am I doing?

19:55.594 --> 19:58.392
(SIGHS) This isn't the way
I want this to happen again.

20:00.432 --> 20:02.764
Leslie, it's not
that big a deal.

20:07.206 --> 20:09.538
I think you should
go home, Mark.

20:10.576 --> 20:12.100
All right, okay.

20:13.011 --> 20:14.444
I'm sorry.

20:15.380 --> 20:16.870
I'm gonna get out of here.
Yeah.

20:16.949 --> 20:18.940
(CHUCKLING) I'm sorry.
It's okay, it's...

20:19.017 --> 20:20.211
No. Oh, my God!

20:20.285 --> 20:22.845
(EXCLAIMING) Oh, my God!

20:22.921 --> 20:25.321
LESLIE: Oh, my God!
Mark, are you all right?

20:25.390 --> 20:26.448
ANDY: Wow.

20:26.525 --> 20:29.358
(GROANS) Are you okay?
Oh, my God!

20:30.262 --> 20:31.627
MARK: Go get some help.
LESLIE: Help!

20:31.697 --> 20:32.925
MARK: Go get some help.
LESLIE: Help!

20:32.998 --> 20:33.987
MARK: Go get some help.
LESLIE: Help!

20:34.066 --> 20:37.194
(LAUGHING) Hey, babe!
Baby, open up!

20:37.803 --> 20:39.862
That guy Mark
just fell in the pit!

20:41.006 --> 20:42.598
What?
You know that guy Mark?

20:42.674 --> 20:44.471
Yeah.
He just fell in the pit!

20:44.543 --> 20:45.805
You gotta go check it out.
You're a nurse.

20:45.877 --> 20:47.435
I think he'd
probably be hurt.

20:50.349 --> 20:51.907
(LAUGHING) Seriously,
it's pretty bad!

20:51.984 --> 20:56.080
<i>(AND Y SINGING)</i>
<i>Pit! I fell in it, the pit</i>

20:56.755 --> 20:59.315
<i>You fell in it, the pit</i>

20:59.725 --> 21:04.890
<i>We all fell in it, the pit</i>

21:04.963 --> 21:09.195
<i>The pit!</i>
<i>I fell in it, the pit</i>

